  "description": [
    "No trees were allowed to grow near the small village in Northern Korea where little Korea lived for fear of the tigers Last year the tigers had come and taken off tt man and woman sleeping quietly on a mat near the open door and the villagers might possibly have saved them had it not been for the trees among which they escaped with their prey so the trees were all cut down That was the reason that Koreas little home stood out so bare and prom inent on the edge of the village once so thickly wooded Little Korea had been up an hour before the rest of the family getting ready the usual 10 oclock breakfast when her father called her He looked wearied and worried as she went into his apartment and as if he had not slept all night long Korea made her humble little bow folded her hands and east down her Korea Cast Down Her EjM eyes as she entered his august pres ence 1 have an errand for yen he said tersely 1 shall enjoy doing it she respond ed according to Korean etiquette Its well to say so answered her father because"
  ],
